      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Sequester for Congressional Pay and Accountability Act - Amends the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act of 1985 (Gramm-Rudman-Hollings Act) to reduce the pay of each Member of Congress by the greatest percentage by which the pay of any federal employee is reduced as a result of a furlough relating to the sequestration order for that furlough period.</p> <p>Defines &quot;furlough period&quot; as each period:</p> <ul> <li> beginning on the effective date of the first furlough of any federal employee relating to a sequestration order issued under the Gramm-Rudman-Hollings Act, and</li> <li>ending on the last day of the fiscal year to which the sequestration order applies.</li> </ul>]]></text>
